---
source: crates/kea-infer/tests/diagnostic_snapshots.rs
expression: out
---
E0001: type_mismatch — Expression type does not match expected type.
E0002: missing_field — A required record or row field is missing.
E0003: duplicate_field — A record or row field is declared more than once.
E0004: lacks_violation — A row-polymorphism lacks constraint was violated.
E0005: undefined_name — A referenced variable, function, or name is undefined.
E0006: syntax — Source text does not parse as valid Kea syntax.
E0007: non_exhaustive — Pattern matching is missing one or more cases.
E0008: purity_violation — An impure operation was used in a pure-only context.
E0009: arity_mismatch — A function was called with the wrong number of arguments.
E0010: trait_bound — A required trait bound is not satisfied for the given type.
E0011: extra_field — A record or row contains a field not allowed in this context.
E0012: type_error — General type checking error.
E0801: missing_annotation — A required declaration-boundary type annotation is missing.
W1001: missing_module_doc — A public module has no module-level doc block.
E0013: record_row_mismatch — Record fields do not match: the value has missing or extra fields.
E0014: effect_row_mismatch — Function effect row does not match: body performs effects not in the signature.
E0015: unhandled_effect — An effect is required by the function body but not declared in the signature.
E0016: unused_handler — A handler clause covers an effect the expression does not perform.
E0017: catch_type_mismatch — `catch` result type does not match the Fail error type.
